owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A characteristic of a Project, Model, or Dataset. Whenever possible, values should link to other ontologies or controlled vocabularies.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Descriptor

owl:Class.rdfs:comment:
The key top-level entity of the ontology. A Project is described by the Detail entities (Author, Date, Comments, etc.) and is comprised of zero or more Models and zero or more Datasets.
Thus, a Project can encapsulate a model and its data, a model only, or a dataset.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Project

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An individual (human) author. Ideally should have a link to a unique identifier such as the ORCiD identifier.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Individual author

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Site count

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "The following questions are primarily intended to encourage dataset creators to clearly articulate their reasons for creating the dataset and to promote transparency about funding interests. The latter may be particularly relevant for datasets created for research purposes."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Motivation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "For what purpose was the dataset created? Was there a specific task in mind? Was there a specific gap that needed to be filled?"
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dataset purpose

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Specify grantor, grant name, and number.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Funding

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "Who created the dataset (for example, which team, research group) and on behalf of which entity (for example, company, institution, organization)?"
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dataset creation team

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "What do the instances that comprise the dataset represent (for example, documents, photos, people, countries)? Are there multiple types of instances (for example, movies, users, and ratings; people and interactions between them; nodes and edges)?"
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Data type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "How many instances are there in total (of each type, if appropriate)?"
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Number of instances

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "Does the dataset contain all possible instances or is it a sample (not necessarily random) of instances from a larger set? If the dataset is a sample, then what is the larger set? Is the sample representative of the larger set (for example, geographic coverage)? If so, please describe how this representativeness was validated/verified. If it is not representative of the larger set, please describe why not (for example, to cover a more diverse range of instances, because instances were withheld or unavailable)."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Representativeness

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "23. If the dataset is a sample from a larger set, what was the sampling strategy (for example, deterministic, probabilistic with specific sampling probabilities)?"
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sample type

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "Is there a label or target associated with each instance? If so, please provide a description."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Labeling

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "Is any information missing from individual instances? If so, please provide a description, explaining why this information is missing (for example, because it was unavailable). This does not include intentionally removed information, but might include, for example, redacted text."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Missing information

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "Are relationships between individual instances made explicit (for example, social network links)? If so, please describe how these relationships are made explicit."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Relationships between instances

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "Are there recommended data splits (for example, training, development/validation, testing)? If so, please provide a description of these splits, explaining the rationale behind them."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Partitions

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describe any errors, sources of noise, or redundancies in the dataset.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Noise

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "Is the dataset self-contained, or does it link to or otherwise rely on external resources (for example, websites, tweets, other datasets)? If it links to or relies on external resources, a) are there guarantees that they will exist, and remain constant, over time; b) are there official archival versions of the complete dataset (that is, including the external resources as they existed at the time the dataset was created); c) are there any restrictions (for example, licenses, fees) associated with any of the external resources that might apply to a dataset consumer? Please provide descriptions of all external resources and any restrictions associated with them, as well as links or other access points, as appropriate."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: External data

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "Does the dataset contain data that might be considered confidential (for example, data that is protected by legal privilege or by doctor–patient confidentiality, data that includes the content of individuals’ non-public communications)? If so, please provide a description."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Confidentiality

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "17. Does the dataset identify any subpopulations (for example, by age, gender)? If so, please describe how these subpopulations are identified and provide a description of their respective distributions within the dataset."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Subpopulations

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "18. Is it possible to identify individuals (that is, one or more natural persons), either directly or indirectly (that is, in combination with other data) from the dataset? If so, please describe how."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Re-identification

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: "19. Does the dataset contain data that might be considered sensitive in any way (for example, data that reveals race or ethnic origins, sexual orientations, religious beliefs, political opinions or union memberships, or locations; financial or health data; biometric or genetic data; forms of government identification, such as social security numbers; criminal history)? If so, please provide a description."
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sensitive data

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describe ethical review of project, model, and/or dataset by Institutional Review Board or other review body.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Ethical review
